verses:
Where the paschal blood is poured, Death's dark angel sheathes the sword;
Isreal's hosts triumphant go Through the wave that drowns the foe.
Praise we Christ whose blood was shed, Paschal 
victim, paschal bread;
With sincerity and love Eat we manna from above.

Mighty Victim from the sky, Hell's fierce power beneath you lie;
You have conquered in the fight, You have brought us life and light;
Now no more can death appall, Now no more the grave 
enthral1;
You have opened Paradise, And in you the saints shall rise.
